site_name: Part of Plantation Wharf, York Place, Gartons Way, SW11 3UF (Plantation Wharf)
description: Demolition of existing buildings (with the exception of Trade Tower) and redevelopment of the site to provide a mixed-use development comprising Class A uses (A1 -shops, A2 -financial and professional services, A3 - restaurants and cafes, A4 - drinking establishments), Class B1 (office), Class D1/D2 (non-residential institution/assembly and leisure floorspace) and flexible uses across Classes A1/A2/A3/A4/B1/D1/D2 and 127 residential units (as affordable and market housing), contained within four new buildings 5-, 6-, 8-, and 16-storeys high, and including erection of 6-storey extension at the top of Trade Tower (following removal of level 13) to provide a net increase of 8 residential units.  Provision of private amenity space and public open space, car and cycle parking, and creation of publically accessible square at the base of Trade Tower and Port House to link to Coral Row route to the River Thames.  Alterations and extensions to the basement level to provide cycle parking, plant rooms and refuse storage.
